This paper deals with the phase transitions of convex optimization methods in signal recovery, which is a topic that falls under several sub-categories of computer science. 

cs.IT (Information Theory) is the most likely sub-category as it deals with the mathematical foundations of signal processing and communication. 

cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also likely as the paper mentions machine learning in the abstract and the phase transitions of convex optimization methods are important in machine learning. 

cs.CV (Computer Vision) is another likely sub-category as total variation minimization is commonly used in image processing and computer vision. 

cs.NA (Numerical Analysis) is a possible sub-category as the paper deals with the numerical optimization of convex functions. 

cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is a less likely sub-category as the paper does not explicitly mention social or information networks, but the topic of signal recovery is relevant to network analysis.
